lines.append('## What The Re-Audit Changes In Practical Terms\n')
for n in ['The row you called out for `phi-gamma-delta-main / sigma-tau-chapter-university-of-washington / find_instagram` did **not** mean the system searched Sigma Chi for Fiji. It meant the job executed **zero chapter-specific external queries** because the batch-level provider-health probe bundle had already collapsed. The old report used the wrong evidence label.','The most repeated table values in the old report happened because different evidence layers were being collapsed into a single `query path` column. In this report, the repeated parts are moved into section-level notes and only job-specific context stays in the row.','The system’s biggest problem during the stress window was not “it searched the wrong chapter over and over.” The larger issue was that too many invalid historical rows existed in the queue at all, and that provider degradation made even good search strategies expensive when not short-circuited.','The new architecture held up: backend-owned queue control, typed deferred states, repair containment, and school/activity validation all materially improved the system during the same run.']: lines.append(f'1. {n}' if not lines[-1].startswith('1.') else f'2. {n}')
